body:
### Description

Hi, first of all, thx for this amazing library! I've been using it for some time now without any issues up until now that I'm building in release mode.  The code snippet below works perfectly in Debug mode but not Release, where it's raising an exception when calling SKTypeface.FromStream(stream) (stack trace details down below)

Am I missing anything or should I change this approach?

Thanks in advance!

### Code
    using (var asset = App.assets.Open($"fonts/someFont.otf"))
    {
        var fontStream = new MemoryStream();
        asset.CopyTo(fontStream);
        fontStream.Flush();
        fontStream.Position = 0;
        typeface = SKTypeface.FromStream(fontStream);
        if(typeface != null)
        {
            //Do something...
        }
    }

### Expected Behavior

typeface form returned without exception

### Actual Behavior

Exception raised in release mode only.

### Basic Information

- Version with issue:  1.60.0
- IDE:  VS 2017 Enterprise 15.6.6
- Platform Target Frameworks: API 25 (Android 7.1)
  - Android:  Testing on a 6.0 android device.
- Target Devices:
  -   Honor 8



### Stack trace details

05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747): Stacktrace:
05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747): 
05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747):   at <unknown> <0xffffffff>
05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747):   at (wrapper managed-to-native) SkiaSharp.SkiaApi.sk_typeface_create_from_stream (intptr,int) <0x0003b>
05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747):   at SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.FromStream (SkiaSharp.SKStreamAsset,int) [0x00018] in <5a812555f55f40c0a29350793a12a8ac>:0
05-15 00:23:48.144 E/mono-rt ( 2747):   at SkiaSharp.SKTypeface.FromStream (System.IO.Stream,int) [0x00019] in <5a812555f55f40c0a29350793a12a8ac>:0
